<br>
The members of the High Council had all gathered around in the chamber room of the guild hall of the Emerald Phoenix to convene for their monthly roundtable discussion. As they were talking about the goings on in the guild there came a knock on upon the chamber room door.<br>
<br>
Squire Feudil dismissed himself from the side of Lady Larisian to see what this interruption was about. He opened the door and left the room to return a few seconds later.<br>
<br>
&quot;M'Lady&quot;, said Squire Feudil, &quot;Two of the guilds scouts have returned from their scouting mission.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye,&quot; responded Lady Larisian.<br>
<br>
&quot;They wish to make a report to you. They say that is a matter of urgency otherwise they would have averted from interrupting your meeting.&quot;<br>
<br>
A hushed exchanged of words circled the chambers between the council members gathered as the two rouges entered the room.<br>
<br>
They strode into the room side-by-side silently and smoothly stopping at the head of the council table. The members of the council knew these two scouts well.<br>
<br>
Sir Jarar Dieberi and Lady Imoen Soulseeker, both around the same age, both kneeled before the council then rose to address those assembled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well Met Sir Jarar and Lady Imoen. What news do you bring to us?&quot; asked Lady Larisian.<br>
<br>
Sir Jarar spoke first. All of the council members stared in the scouts direction in wait of was to be said<br>
<br>
&quot;M'lady, members of the High Council, I bring news that does not bode well for the realm of Norrath nor Emerald Phoenix. During our recent scouting mission to the outlying areas of Innothule swamp Lady Imoen and I infiltrated a camp of Ogres disguised as Dark Elves. We passed ourselves off as travelers to Ogguk. During our stay with this camp we discovered that a group of Ogres, Trolls, and Dark Elves known as the Severed Souls is planning to bring darkness to our realm.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, M'lady,&quot; interjected Lady Imoen, &quot;There numbers at this time are not known and their plans as to when and where were not revealed to us. They are led by a one Rukkas Bashimgud (sp?), an Ogre.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah so his threat has come to pass,&quot; sighed Lady Larisian.<br>
<br>
&quot;What threat might that be M'Lady?&quot; asked Lady Tarnia.<br>
<br>
&quot;I ran in to Rukkas in Oasis of Marr on day while traveling. He was alone at the time so posed no threat to me. As I slipped behind a tent of gypsies and used my hide discipline I could see him sniffing at the air. I did not move for fear of being found out but I soon found out it did not matter.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Me kan smel uz lity. Me not noze wher uz iz but me noze a forist smel shud not b in du sand. Me noze that u not gud to ogur. Me not git uz now, but me promiz me git utterz and com bac to git uz&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;He then went along his way, constantly sniffing the air to make sure that he was not being followed. I really thought nothing of it at the time and quickly forgot about the incident.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It is too bad I was not with you that day M'Lady!, exclaimed Lady Tarnia. &quot;We could have cut him into little pieces. Sir Stormwynd would have loved to practice his cooking skills with Ogre meat. Albeit it would not be fit for consumption by us but our Squires Misha and Ivan would have ate like kings.&quot;<br>
<br>
The council let out a laugh at Lady Tarnias remarks about her Squires and eating like kings.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir Jarar and Lady Imoen....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye M'lady,&quot; they said in unison.<br>
<br>
&quot;I would like you take leave of us for now. The High Council will discuss this possible invasion of Dark Ones into our territory.&quot;<br>
