<br>
     Trevalyn stared at the small rusty blood stained blade obsessively.  His eyes never moving from it.  Until a knock sounded from the door of his home, breaking him from the concentration.  He rose from his seat, adorning his civilian garb.  As he opened the door, he saw nothing.  Knowing who it was, he left the door open and went back to his seat.   Suddenly the door slammed shut and a small breeze went by Trevalyn.  Obviously someone has moved behind him.  <br>
<br>
     &quot;Show yourself to me gnome.&quot;<br>
<br>
     His order only answered with silence.  <br>
<br>
     &quot;show yourself gnome or i shall return you to the Tower of the Spurned to recieve your punishement.&quot;<br>
<br>
    At that moment a gnome materialized in front of Trevalyn, already on his knees begging his forgiveness speaking a mile a minute.<br>
<br>
     &quot;Im so sorry Knight Templar, i didnt mean to disreguard your order, i wouldnever do that i dont know how i could live, if it wasnt for your generaosity i definatle be dead or worse those tower of the spurned are cruel even comparably for dark elves i mean they really had it for me...&quot;<br>
<br>
     Trevalyn wearily rose a hand to silence the stuttering fool.  &quot;Silence.  have you completed the mission i have asked of thee?&quot; Trevalyn asked coldly as his eyes had found their focal point again on the rusty broad sword.<br>
 <br>
     The gnome fidgeted nervously, &quot;uhh, mission my Knight Templar?&quot;<br>
<br>
     Trevalyn let out a sigh of dissapointment as he removed a small flask from the cupboard which looked as if were filled with blood.  He removed its top and handed it to the confused gnome.<br>
<br>
     &quot;drink, small one&quot;<br>
<br>
     the gnome carefully studdied the bottle, &quot;umm..aye, Templar i will&quot;<br>
<br>
     The gnome slowly began to sip on the flask of blood.  As he did it began to flow with a blue light.  As the light grew brighter, the gnome drank greedier in larger gulps until the cask was empty.  Suddenly the gnomes form began to morph and glow.  The light became blinding in the room.  Trevalyn hardly noticed as he squinted a bit while never removing his gaze from the blade.  <br>
<br>
     As the light receeded, no longer was a gnome standing before Trevalyn... but a Teir'dal.  <br>
<br>
     Temptus took a breath and a sigh of relief he that he was released from his curse for a few moments thanks to the bottle of clarity ridden elder enchanters blood that Trevalyn gave him.  <br>
<br>
     &quot;Thankyou Templar.  I have completed the mission you asked of me.  I have reports and accurate accounts of the battle that has begun between Severed Souls and the cursed Emerald Phoenix.  I have also obtained vital information reguarding the Emerald Phoenix's ranks and strengths and weaknesses.  They felt no threat from the gnome around their ranks and bases of opperaton, nor could they see the eye watching them in battle as it was my sight binded to theirs.  It was... enlightening.&quot;<br>
<br>
     Trevalyn finally drew his gaze away from the blade, studying his servant.  &quot;And what would be your recommendation, Temptus?&quot;<br>
<br>
     &quot;I beleieve, Templar, that the Nation could benefit much from this war.  It began over a duo of fools from the Paleones and is slowly growing into a full fledged war.  I believe that our Dark bretheren the Severed souls and their orkhalla would benefit and even be welcome to our assistence.&quot;<br>
<br>
     Trevalyn raised an eyebrow at his servant. &quot;and did you meet with the Orkhalla?&quot;<br>
<br>
     &quot;I... attempted to, Templar.  But he was not privy to the knowledge of my true form.  I had to avoid... being eaten..&quot;<br>
<br>
     Trevalyn chuckled at the thought, much to the annoyance of his servant.<br>
<br>
     &quot;Come now Temptus.  You have succeeded in your mission perfectly.  And for that accomplishment, i shall give you another vile of the enchanter's blood.  You shall stave off your curse for another few days.  Now come, dictate this letter to the Orkhalla.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
     Vendui, Mighty Orkhalla Rukkas of the tribe Severed Souls,<br>
<br>
     Do not mind my servant as he may be in a fit of madness.  Please do not eat him, as he is not what he seems and his death would mean dire repercussions from Neriak.  I have a proposition which may be most beneficial for both our Tribes.  Return word with my servant.  And worry not, he knows the consequences for not obeying me no matter what form he may be in.  May we find eachother quickly.  Good hunting and may the father watch over the Severed Souls.<br>
<br>
Trevalyn Phliths'Elgluth<br>
Head of the Household of Phliths'Elgluth<br>
Buddon Dette Allore<br>
Knight Templar of the Nation of Eridine&quot;<br>
<br>
    &quot;Now get this letter to him as quickly as possible Temptus.  Not just quickly because of its importance, but because the supply of blood i gave you will not last more then a day or two.  move with haste.&quot;<br>
<br>
     Temptus scrolled the letter up avoiding his masters gaze.  &quot;Aye Templar, i shall move quickly&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
     Temptus quickly left the Templars home.  Trevalyn sat, quietly contemplating the events to come.  The flowing blood that will result would only be outdone by the screams of pain, terror, and hate as the Nation would ground its enemies into the ground.  At these thoughts, a smile came to his face.  Much glory indeed.  Trevalyn stood, put on his armor, picked up his weapon and made his way for the Eridani guildhall.  The first house would need to approve the plan, which he had no doubt they would.  <br>
<br>
     Much blood...much blood indeed..<br>
<br>
